    "head_commit": {
      "id": "0806bd90864009d4a829ddf7ab1be6f8042f2d05",
      "message": "Unauthorized error handling refactorings (#14837)\n\nFixes https://github.com/enso-org/cloud-v2/issues/2291\n\nQuite a lot of changes:\n- Fixed handling of 401 errors to be centralized and consisted.\n- Multi-stage session recovery flow:\n- Queries and mutations that face 401 errors trigger single-flight session refresh with multiple backed-off attempts. In general, 401 failures no longer cause unbounded retries.\n- If session refresh fails, we immediately logout\n- If session refresh succeeds, we replay failed queries/mutations _once_. We report error if 401 failures continue for some time.\n- Logout redirect logic is more robust: the flow is also single-flight, `replace` is used instead of `push` to avoid polluting history\n- Unit tests for most of the problematic scenarios.",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-03T12:19:47Z",
      "author": {
        "name": "Ilya Bogdanov"
      }
    }
  },
